Description: Skip signed-EFI build artifacts
 efitools' Makefile builds EFISIGNED = $(patsubst %.efi,%-signed.efi,$(EFIFILES))
 by invoking sbsign on each unsigned %.efi. sbsign comes from sbsigntool,
 which declares efitools as a build dep — creating a cyclic dep when
 efitools is built first.
 .
 The signed EFI binaries are test fixtures: signed with auto-generated
 ephemeral PK/KEK/DB keys (created by openssl req at build time, random
 per build). Users can't use them — the signing keys are throwaway. Per
 the Prime Directive, shipping fixtures with no user value is complexity
 that doesn't serve the user.
 .
 Replace $(EFISIGNED) with $(EFIFILES) in the all: target. The install:
 rule already only ships $(EFIFILES) (unsigned); the *-signed.efi were
 never going to be installed anyway. This breaks the dep cycle without
 reordering the graph or introducing pre-built sbsign into the chroot.
Author: InterGenOS project, 2026-05-03
Origin: vendor (InterGenOS)

--- a/Makefile
+++ b/Makefile
@@ -27,7 +27,7 @@ EXTERNALKEYS = ms-uefi ms-kek

 EFISIGNED = $(patsubst %.efi,%-signed.efi,$(EFIFILES))

-all: $(EFISIGNED) $(BINARIES) $(MANPAGES) noPK.auth $(KEYAUTH) \
+all: $(EFIFILES) $(BINARIES) $(MANPAGES) noPK.auth $(KEYAUTH) \
 	$(KEYUPDATEAUTH) $(KEYBLACKLISTAUTH) $(KEYHASHBLACKLISTAUTH)


